<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddc244065-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06" identifier="/us/usc/t12/s1734"><num value="1734">§ 1734.</num><heading> Amendment, extension, or increase of commitment amounts</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">At any time prior to final endorsement for insurance, the Secretary, in his discretion, may amend, extend, or increase the amount of any commitment, provided the mortgage, as finally endorsed for insurance is eligible for insurance under the provisions of this chapter and the rules and regulations thereunder, in effect at the time the original commitment to insure was issued.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddc244066-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">(<ref href="/us/act/1934-06-27/ch847">June 27, 1934, ch. 847</ref>, title V, § 515 as added <ref href="/us/act/1949-10-25/ch729/s3">Oct. 25, 1949, ch. 729, § 3</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/63/906">63 Stat. 906</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/90/19/s1/a/3">Pub. L. 90–19, § 1(a)(3)</ref>, <date date="1967-05-25">May 25, 1967</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/81/17">81 Stat. 17</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/98/479/tII/s204/a/20">Pub. L. 98–479, title II, § 204(a)(20)</ref>, <date date="1984-10-17">Oct. 17, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/2232">98 Stat. 2232</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
